Version 2.11:
- [!] 26 Mar 2007, Sheriff - Bug (0009957): The "Auth" charge type was not sent correctly during the payment transaction. Fixed.
- [!] 19 Mar 2007, Sheriff - Bug (0017935): HSBC response verification procedure didn't take into account "currency" code, as a result a trunsaction was marked as "failed". Fixed.

Version 2.10:
- [+] 08 Jan 2007, Sheriff - Improvement (0011464): HSBC response verification procedure was improved.

Version 2.9:
- [+] 14 Nov 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0013099): An ability to handle very long customer login names was added (if a login had been longer than 32 characters, it used to be handled incorrectly on the HSBC side).
- [!] 13 Nov 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0013096): The existing order statuses were changed incorrectly in the "HSBC settings" section. Fixed.

Version 2.8:
- [!] 11 Oct 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0011935): The existing order statuses were assigned for each type of HSBC's reply, not taking into account the order substatuses which were introduced by the AOM module. Fixed.

Version 2.7:
- [+] 19 Sep 2006, Osipov - Improvement (0010198): It is now possible to assign an existing LiteCommerce order status for each type of reply from HSBC (Queued, Processed, Failed/Declined/Canceled). 
- [+] 19 Sep 2006, Osipov - Improvement (0009957): Charge Type (Auth / Capture) selection option added on module configuration page.

Version 2.6:
- [+] 08 Aug 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0008689): The ability to work with orders flagged by Fraud Shield was added.

Version 2.5:
- [+] 27 Jul 2006, Osipov - Improvement: Improved user-entered data checkup.

Version 2.4:
- [!] 21 Sep 2005, Sheriff, Asd - Bug (0008637): A few misspellings were fixed.
- [!] 08 Jul 2005, Asd - Bug (0005335): Billing and shipping counties were sent as numbers instead of names of the counties. Fixed.
- [!] 07 Mar 2005, Asd - Bug: The compiled code/templates cache was not cleaned up during the module uninstallation. Fixed.

Version 2.3

 - [!] 02 Mar 2005, Asd - Bug: The incorrect paths to the module part caused incompatibility between the module and LiteCommerce ASP. Fixed.
